    "body": "FWIW, I recently was using besu with remix and figured I would add some color to this issue.  I *was* able to connect to a local besu instance using the \"Web3 provider\" URL, but when it connects, remix does not have any accounts to use.  For this option remix is expecting a geth node which has a local account.  Besu does not have a concept of local accounts and it expects all transactions sent through it to be pre-signed.\r\n\r\nThe best way I found to use besu with remix is to use the \"Injected Web3 Provider\" option, with metamask.  I configured metamask to point to my local besu instance and it worked seamlessly (and allows you to use any private key you have configured with metamask)",
